http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 14 May 2014
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2014; 27(20) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapEventSummary&reportid=15241


Foot-and-mouth disease, Tunisia
-------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 13 May 2014 from Dr Hichem Bouzghaia, [Director General, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture], Tunis, Tunisia

Summary
Report type: follow-up report No. 2
Date of start of the event 25 Apr 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 26 Apr 2014
Report date: 13 May 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 13 May 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: Mar 1999
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (14)
For the details pertaining to each of the 14 new outbreaks, spread throughout the 6 governorates of Ariana, Kairouan, Sidi Bouzid, Kasserine, Monastir, and Nabeul, please refer to the source URL above, which also includes a map of outbreak locations. - Mod.AS]

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 14
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 459 / 20 / 0 / 0 / 1
Sheep / 606 / 111 / 0 / 0 / 0
Goats / 30 / 2 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics (rates apparent, expressed as percentages):
Species / morbidity rate / / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 4.36 / 0 / 0 / 0.22 /
Sheep / 18.32 / 0 / 0 / 0 /
Goats / 6.67 / 0 / 0 / 0 /
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Illegal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments:
In addition to the control measures mentioned, the following measures are being implemented: crisis cells at national and regional levels; burying of the [offal] and bones between 3 layers of lime; disinfection of vehicles leaving the affected governorates; vaccination points of susceptible species at the entrance of livestock markets [comment]; epidemiological investigation to determine the origin of the infection; communication plan.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine, movement control inside the country, vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s), modified stamping out, no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Veterinary Research Institute (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 29 Apr 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to this follow-up report, the serotype involved is FMDV serotype O. Genotyping results may be helpful in identifying the source of this epizootic and the most relevant vaccine strains. - Mod.AS

Maps of Tunisia can be seen at http://www.planetware.com/i/map/TUN/tunisia-map.jpg and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2474624,71. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
